HEADWORD: Impastation
<hw>Im`pas*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Impaste</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of making into paste; that which
is formed into a paste or mixture; specifically, a combination of
different substances by means of cements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

